  setup:
    One-time configuration of the front host.

    setup init: parses the backend address (IPv4/IPv6),
    generates a self-signed TLS certificate, extracts the
    bundled wstunnel binary, generates a secret, renders
    systemd units, and writes parameters to SQLite. Does
    not start services.

    setup clean yes=true: stops services, removes unit files,
    certificates, binary, and the database.

    setup status: reports configuration state.

    setup init refuses to run when a configuration already
    exists. setup clean is required before reconfiguring.

  ghost:
    Lifecycle of the wstunnel + socat egress pair.

    ghost start: enables the wstunnel unit; systemd
    dependencies pull in the egress unit automatically.
    ghost stop: stops both.
    ghost restart: egress first, then wstunnel.
    ghost status: systemctl queries + SQLite parameters.
    ghost client_config: emits the [Wstunnel] block.
    ghost client_command: emits the wstunnel CLI command.

    client_config and client_command output contains the
    <FRONTMATTER-PUBLIC-IP> placeholder; the operator
    replaces it with front's public address.


Systemd integration:

  Both data-path services run as systemd units under
  Restart=always.

    phantom-frontmatter-ghost-wstunnel.service
      Type=simple. CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE for port :443.
      ProtectSystem=strict.
      Requires=phantom-frontmatter-ghost-egress.service,
      After=phantom-frontmatter-ghost-egress.service
      BindsTo=phantom-frontmatter-ghost-egress.service

    phantom-frontmatter-ghost-egress.service
      Type=simple. Forwards loopback UDP to the backend
      address via socat. IPv4 backends use UDP4, IPv6
      backends use UDP6 with bracket notation. Hardening
      directives: NoNewPrivileges, ProtectSystem=strict,
      MemoryDenyWriteExecute.

  Compact lifecycle binding:
    systemctl enable --now ghost-wstunnel pulls in the egress
    unit and waits for it before starting wstunnel. BindsTo=
    links the two together: egress down cascades to wstunnel.
    ghost restart bounces egress first, then wstunnel.


